items.title: Trips to Costa Del Sol in 2005, 2007, 2008, 2010 & 2011 - Costa Del Sol Trips: Mijas
items.summary: During the years of 2005, 2007, 2008, 2010 & 2011 I made…
items.content_html:
During the years of 2005, 2007, 2008, 2010 & 2011 I made five trips to the Costa Del Sol in Spain. Staying in Torremolinos, my first trip there joined by my Dad in 2005, and then staying in Benalmadena for the following four trips, twice with friends and twice solo trips. Iâ€™ve found it to be the perfect cheaper overseas travel location in the past, great weather even in the winter months we get over here in England, cool but still hot in Southern Spain, and flying into Malaga you get to see that great city and also travel down to the seaside towns of Torremolinos, Benalmadena, Fuengirola and the beautiful white-washed village of Mijas.

I didnâ€™t have much of a clue with taking pictures at this point and as noted above the cameras I used were very basic point & shoots but nonetheless they bring back some good memories of my travels around the Costa Del Sol â€“ enjoy!

Note: These photos were taken with the following low quality cameras!

items.title: Australia & Thailand Trip 2004 ~ Part One
items.summary: In March 2004 myself and a friend set off to visit Australia,…
items.content_html:
In March 2004 myself and a friend set off to visit Australia, particularly Melbourne to visit a mutual friend &Â expatÂ Rob who moved over there a year earlier, we also stayed in Sydney for about a week where my travelling buddy Simon had arranged to travel up the coast so I had a few days to myself before I flew home via Singapore.

Before reaching Oz we planned to visit Thailand for a week as well, which was just amazing and full of surprises (we even bumped into some old friends of mine whilst we were over there, a couple I know who were having some sort of argument in a bus bookings office! ended up travelling out of sweltering Bangkok down to the islands with them, although we were lucky to make it in one piece due to a very dodgy coach driver who what seemed to be on some local â€˜pick-me-upâ€™ drug that kept him from noticing a burst tire for quite some time! thereâ€™s a pic of that tire in the photos belowâ€¦). I did take a camera with me (and a video camcorder), a pretty rubbish point & shoot one though and set on the smallest resolution hence sizeâ€™s of the photos, and Iâ€™ve organized them here in these slider galleryâ€™s to make viewing a lot easierâ€¦

Thailand & Singapore Photos

After relaxing on the beaches of Thailand for a week we flew to Melbourne, Australia to meet our expat friend & skater Rob!

Melbourne Photos

Rob took us to some great skateparks and we had a lot of fun on those wooden planks! but as the saying goes â€˜All good things must come to an endâ€™Â and the stack I took at the end in one of those parks actually was quite a painful scrape I can tell you! still got a tiny scar on my arm as a memoryâ€¦
